<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="002" project="github-actions-rationalization-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Investigate post-PR-#314 master CI failure (run 26755019759)</title>
    <phase>0: Inventory + Baseline</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>ci-cd, github-actions, devops, root-cause, decision-record</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Root-cause investigation produces decision record; no source code modified; explicit acceptance from spec FR-02</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Investigate the master CI failure on run 26755019759 (Build step + Prettier failure observed 2026-06-01 12:31 UTC post-PR-#314). Determine whether it's an environment-related transient (CI runner difference) OR an actual regression. Either fix it OR document it as deferred with explicit rationale. The disposition is recorded in `decisions/D-01-master-ci-failure-disposition.md`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform DevOps engineer. Comfortable reading `gh run view` logs, comparing CI runner environments, and authoring decision records. Familiar with the predecessor project's `decisions/D-NN` pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A decision record exists at `projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/decisions/D-01-master-ci-failure-disposition.md` containing:
    - The root cause of run 26755019759 (or "no clear root cause; transient" with evidence)
    - A disposition: FIXED (with commit ref), DEFERRED (with rationale + follow-up), or RESOLVED-TRANSIENT (no action needed)
    - If FIXED: a follow-up PR ref OR a commit on this branch
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-02 + Risk R1: this is a project-blocker if `sdap-ci.yml` remains broken on master post-PR-#314. The failure was Build (Release config) + Prettier formatting issue. Need to determine if it's environment vs regression. Phase 1 fix tasks (010/011/012) should proceed independently, but if this is a real regression, the project must pause Phase 1 to address it.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml</file>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/decisions/D-01-master-ci-failure-disposition.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-02: Must either fix OR document with rationale</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-01: Investigation only — if a real regression in `src/`, document and route to product backlog (do NOT fix `src/` in this project)</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-03: If a fix requires disabling `enforce_admins`, log it in `decisions/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Decision record follows predecessor's `decisions/D-NN-{topic}.md` format</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/ci-cd-workflow.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Fetch failure details: `gh run view 26755019759 --log-failed` (or `--log`). Identify the failing step, exit code, and key log lines.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml` end-to-end. Locate the Build (Release) job + Prettier step. Note runner image, Node version, .NET version.</step>
    <step order="3">Compare against the post-fix expected state: was PR #314's fix limited to the duplicate-key bug, or did it also touch Build/Prettier? Check `git show {PR#314-merge-sha}` for scope.</step>
    <step order="4">Reproduce locally if practical: `npm run format -- --check` (Prettier) and `dotnet build -c Release` to see if same failure surfaces locally. If yes → real regression; if no → environment issue.</step>
    <step order="5">Decision branch:
      - If FIXED: identify the minimal fix (likely Prettier config or staged code already formatted), commit it on this branch in a separate commit, and link the commit SHA in the decision record. NOTE: NFR-01 forbids `src/` changes if the regression is in `src/` code itself — in that case, route to product backlog and mark DEFERRED.
      - If DEFERRED: write rationale, identify owner + target date for follow-up, link to a product-backlog issue if one is needed.
      - If RESOLVED-TRANSIENT: cite evidence (e.g., a subsequent master run that succeeded; runner image bump).
    </step>
    <step order="6">Author `decisions/D-01-master-ci-failure-disposition.md` with: title, date, context, evidence, disposition, follow-up. Cross-link from `baseline/workflow-inventory-2026-06-01.md` (if task 001 is complete; otherwise the inventory will link here).</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 002 status to ✅ completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="gh">View workflow run details + logs</tool>
    <tool name="git">Read PR #314 merge commit</tool>
    <tool name="dotnet">Optionally reproduce Build failure locally</tool>
    <tool name="npm">Optionally reproduce Prettier failure locally</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Write decision record</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/decisions/D-01-master-ci-failure-disposition.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`decisions/D-01-master-ci-failure-disposition.md` exists with required sections: Context, Evidence, Disposition, Follow-up.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Disposition is one of: FIXED (with commit SHA), DEFERRED (with rationale + follow-up), or RESOLVED-TRANSIENT (with evidence).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If FIXED: a new commit on `work/github-actions-rationalization-r1` addresses the issue, AND `dotnet build -c Release` + `npm run format -- --check` succeed locally.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md task 002 status updated to ✅.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Per FR-02 and Risk R1: if this turns out to be a real regression in `src/`, do NOT fix it here (NFR-01 forbids). Mark DEFERRED, file a product-backlog issue, and let the project proceed. The Phase 0 exit-gate is about HAVING a disposition, not about FIXING.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>Load knowledge files. Rigor: STANDARD (investigation produces documentation, not code). Can run in parallel with task 001.</protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
